Defendant Ronald E Parker in court with attorney Nicole M Masnica.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Prosecuting attorney moves to amend to Theft contrary to section 13.102(c)(12)  of the Waukesha County Code of Ordinances.  Court approves amendment.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following: 
- Fine totaling: $267.50 to be paid by November 1, 2015; alternate 5 days Huber
- Defendant may also perform alternate of 25 hours of community service in lieu of payment of costs or fines.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.
- Restitution in the amount of $22.66 to be converted to a Civil Judgment to Pick N Save
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Nicole M Masnica in court.   Defendant Ronald E Parker did not appear.   Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is currently in custody at the Milwaukee House of Correction.  Defense requests plea and sentencing date.  Clerk to prepare an Order to Produce for the next court date.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant to have no contact with victim/witness/business listed in the Criminal Complaint.    Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.
